Plugins for the app Feature	Plugin/Library
Email Notifications	nodemailer, nodemailer-smtp-transport
CSV Export	csv-writer, json2csv, react-csv
CSV Import	csv-parser, multer
Dynamic Data Filtering	lodash, mongoose-aggregate-paginate-v2
Charts and Analytics	recharts, chart.js
Role-Based Access Control	jsonwebtoken, bcrypt, express-jwt
Responsive Design	Material-UI, Bootstrap, Tailwind
APIs Integration	axios, swagger-ui-express
Secure Authentication	bcrypt, helmet, express-rate-limit
Scalability	PM2, Redis


1. first go to the BACKEND file and run "npm install"(this will install all the plugins) 
2. and then run "npm run dev" (to start backend)
3. if there any missing plugins manualy run the missing plaugins ( ex- npm install <missing-plugin>)

4. and then go the the frontend file and then again run "npm install"(this will install all the plugins) 
5. then run "npm start" (to start frontend)
6. if there any missing plugins manualy run the missing plaugins ( ex- npm install <missing-plugin>)